rent danger i saw with this rod was, a Red Con (at lvl.35 and scowling) Skelett crossed my way (name <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=3558">'Lich of Miragul'</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) and it see thru invis... i was able to make a circle around it, keep eyes open for it...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    3. Caza- Lake Rathe</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Enter Lake Rathe from SK or RM.... use levitate, waterstone, and invis...float over the water to the Loc <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +2800 -901</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, at this point start diving... there is a big Hole, swim in it... always straight til you reach the tower at location <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +2785 +130</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->... the rod is in the tower, grab it (invis shoudn't drop) swim away, and gate out... nothing agroed me<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    4. Dena- Dagnor's Cauldron</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Easy Pie... enter Dagnor's Cauldron... Levitate / Invis up.... float to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -890 -740</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, start diving and grab the rod... i saw no mobs nearby <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    5. Ena- Lower Guk</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>IMHO the hardest part of the Quest...<br>I had a friend to help me with this, otherwise i woudn't be able to solve this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>Enter lguk, ask for IvU from a cleric or chanter...make your way to the hand room, and ask someone to train the hand and frog to zone (or get hand/frog killed by someone), while he does that swim up, and grab the rod, and gate out...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    6. Fana- Oasis</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Easy again....use Waterstone / Invis...go near the Spectre Island to the Water, and dive to the loc <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -786 -64</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, there is a tower located 'under' water where the rod can be found... the goblins there shoudn't agro when invis is up, and invis won't drop when you pick the rod up...easy<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    7. Geza- Highpass</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Located at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    -218 +435</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> easy to find... keep invis up when you play a Darkelf, otherwise you could get jumped...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    8. Heda- Qeynos Aqueducts</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Located at No#14 on this Map here : <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eqatlas.com/qeynoscatacombsmap.html">eqatlas.com/qeynoscatacombsmap.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    9. Izah- Neriak</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Located in the Water near <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +8 -807</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in 'Neriak Commons' ... easy to find <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    10. Jaka- Unrest</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Enter Unrest, run til you see the House, go right... there is water, jump in, and stay on the right wall... its a little hidden corner where the rod is....loc is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +520 -290</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br><br>After you got all Rods go back to Everfrost to Location <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    +3033 -2393</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> where the Quest NPC can be found (Sulgar), hail him, ask for the chest, stick all rods inside, combine... and get Staff of the Wheel, and Star of Eyes...<br>Give Staff of Wheel + Star of Eyes to Sulgar to get the Icecomet spell runes...<br><br>Good Luck with this Quest <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Deewee Elvenslayer</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 45th Darkelf Sorceress on Vallon Zek<br><br>Dark for Life ! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=deewee>Deewee</A> at: 3/22/02 12:06:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/1/02 7:53:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROD LOCATIONS, and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> Look in the library under Research Trivials. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uatelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atelen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/Paris/LeftBank/4815/pics/dinovisn.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/2/02 8:06:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ROD LOCATIONS, and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> Make sure you're looking in the Library FORUM<br><br>And on more hint; for all teh underwater rods, opening your inventory underwater (make sure you're in the F10 mode with the grey stone border) will clear away all the underwater murk. <p><img src="http://web.