pell names but once one agros they all do, conn em all and if one sees thru invis you will have to get someone to pullem i guess <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucallissagatecaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Callissa Gatecaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/27/02 4:55:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re ROD LOCATIONS , and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> It is not only the caster goblins that can see invis. Basically, any caster goblin can cast see invis upon himself and other mobs in range, and will do so after a short time after spawn.<br><br>The goblins do not aggro on wolf form though, neither in Oasis nor in Lake Rathetear. <p><B><I><font color="silver"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65423" target="_new">Callissa Gatecaller</a><BR><a href="http://www.graffe.com" target="_new">Channeler</a> of <a href="http://www.refiners-fire.net" target="_new">Refiner's Fire</a><BR><a href="http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846" target="_new">Druzzil Ro</a></I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/14/02 5:51:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re ROD LOCATIONS , and HINTS...</span><hr size=1> Just want to point out that you don't actually have to train Hand 